        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>253</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-002B</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-002B.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Equivalence relation">Equivalence relation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An equivalence relation on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a binary relation, often denoted by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sim ]]></fr:tex>, that is:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:strong>Reflexive</fr:strong>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \sim  x]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Symmetric</fr:strong>: If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \sim  y]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y \sim  x]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y \in  X]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Transitive</fr:strong>: If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \sim  y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y \sim  z]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \sim  z]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y, z \in  X]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>An equivalence relation partitions a set into disjoint <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0084">equivalence classes</fr:link>, where each equivalence class consists of all elements that are equivalent to each other under the relation.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In the context of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002D.xml" addr="FA-002D" title="Lp space">Lp spaces</fr:link>, an important equivalence relation is defined by declaring two functions equivalent if they are equal <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link> (i.e., they differ only on a set of measure zero). This allows us to treat functions that are essentially the same (from an integration perspective) as a single entity in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> spaces.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Common examples of equivalence relations include:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Equality (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[=]]></fr:tex>) on any set</fr:li>
<fr:li>Congruence modulo <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> on integers: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \equiv  b \pmod {n}]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a - b]]></fr:tex> is divisible by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Similarity of matrices: Two matrices <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> are similar if there exists an invertible matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B = P^{-1}AP]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Equality <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link> for measurable functions</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>255</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-001E</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-001E.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem">Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_k : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [-\infty , +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> be a sequence of measurable functions. Suppose that</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>There exists a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001L.xml" addr="FA-001L" title="Measurable function">measurable function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [-\infty , +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n \to  f]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>There exists a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001M.xml" addr="FA-001M" title="Summable">summable</fr:link> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [-\infty , +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f_n(x)| \leq  g(x)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> and for <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost every</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol>
            <fr:p>Then,</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\int  f(x)dx = \lim _{n \to  +\infty } \int  f_n(x)dx}]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>257</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-002D</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-002D.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Lp space">Lp space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E \subset  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001B.xml" addr="FA-001B" title="Measurable set">measurable set</fr:link> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \in  [1, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex>. We call <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}^p(E)]]></fr:tex> the set of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001B.xml" addr="FA-001B" title="Measurable set">measurable</fr:link> functions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f: E \to  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> such that</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||f||_{L^p} < +\infty ]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>Now, we set the following <fr:link type="local" href="FA-002B.xml" addr="FA-002B" title="Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}^p(E)]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f,g \in  \mathcal {L}^p(E)]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \sim  g]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x) = g(x)]]></fr:tex> for <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost every</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  E]]></fr:tex>. We set</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E) = \mathcal {L}^p(E)/\sim ]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E)]]></fr:tex> is the quotient (vector) <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001C.xml" addr="FA-001C" title="Space">space</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}^p(E)]]></fr:tex> through the relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sim ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>For a given <fr:link type="external" href="FA-0084">equivalence class</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[f] \in  L^p(E)]]></fr:tex>, we define the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0018.xml" addr="FA-0018" title="Norm">norm</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[f]]]></fr:tex> as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||f||_{L^p(E)}]]></fr:tex> for an arbitrary representative <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \in  [f]]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>From now on, by abuse of notation, we shall confuse <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[f]]]></fr:tex> and its representative <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001C.xml" addr="FA-001C" title="Space">space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E)]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001C.xml" addr="FA-001C" title="Space">space</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>Note</fr:strong>: The elements of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> spaces are not individual functions in the strictest sense, but rather <fr:strong>equivalence classes of functions</fr:strong>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>259</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-001F</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-001F.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Monotone Convergence Theorem">Monotone Convergence Theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_k : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [0, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> be a sequence of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001L.xml" addr="FA-001L" title="Measurable function">measurable function</fr:link>s. Assume that</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[f_n(x) \leq  f_{n+1}(x) \quad  \text {almost everywhere}]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>Then, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [0, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001B.xml" addr="FA-001B" title="Measurable set">measurable</fr:link> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n \to  f]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link>, and</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\lim _{n \to  +\infty } \int  f_n(x)dx = \int  f(x)dx.}]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>261</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-001G</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-001G.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Riesz-Fisher theorem">Riesz-Fisher theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E \subset  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001B.xml" addr="FA-001B" title="Measurable set">measurable set</fr:link> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \in  [1, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex>. Then the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001C.xml" addr="FA-001C" title="Space">space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E)]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000F.xml" addr="FA-000F" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Moreover, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is a positive integer, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p < +\infty ]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{f_n\}_{n \in  \mathbb {N}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000X.xml" addr="FA-000X" title="Cauchy sequence">Cauchy sequence</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E)]]></fr:tex>, then there exist two functions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f, h \in  L^p(E)]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000R.xml" addr="FA-000R" title="Subsequence">subsequence</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{n_k}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n]]></fr:tex> such that</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f_{n_k}(x)| \leq  h(x)]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{n_k} \to  f]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
            <fr:p><fr:em>Note</fr:em>: The proof uses <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001E.xml" addr="FA-001E" title="Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem">Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem</fr:link>, <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001F.xml" addr="FA-001F" title="Monotone Convergence Theorem">Monotone Convergence Theorem</fr:link></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
